{
  "stem": "4272.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 94,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] So we had-- we had no water at all, and food was very scarce.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 94,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Only what somebody, you know, could save and head home.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 94,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But in the streets, you could not buy anything besides herring and pickles.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 95,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "How long after the start of the war did it take the Germans to arrive in Warsaw?",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, they were coming in almost immediately.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, it didn't take long at all.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I would say in two days they were all over Poland.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 97,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Were you able to contact your parents?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 98,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not until after the war.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 98,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was no way of contacting them during the war.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 98,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But after the war, there was the first bus that was leaving from Warsaw to Plozk.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 98,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And one of my friends went there, and I remember I had my pay for the last week of work.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 98,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I asked her to please bring it to my parents and tell them that I'm alive.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 98,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I had to wait much later for a horse and-- and wagon to travel from Warsaw to Plozk.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 99,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So how long did you have to wait, then, until you'd go to Plozk, from when the Germans came in?",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 100,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I didn't come to Plozk till about the middle of October, I would say.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 100,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the war, of course, broke out the first of September.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 101,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And what happened when you got to Plozk?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, when I got to Plozk, I-- of course, my parents were there, and just my younger sister.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The two brothers and the sister that lived in Warsaw, they were on their way to Russia already to escape Hitler.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I didn't see them until after the war ended.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I was with my younger sister.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
